snippet.textDisplay: I left India 13 years back. I use reside in a building/apartment where 90% people were marwadi and only 2 Gujarati in the building including me. This song reminds me of my childhood days where Everyone around me use to speak this beautiful language, I learned it quite a bit , this rajansthani food smell during lunch time. Dal baati every sunday… my neighboring aunty named Azad aunty use to bring me Dal baati every single  Sunday  so I don’t have to eat my mom’s Dal dhokli and here I’m after 13 years still can’t beat that dal baati taste in any restaurant or making myself a gazillion times at home. This makes me miss this adolescent kid in me. This song is beautiful and singer has beautifully sung it. I Miss India
